            },
            "answer_text": "Yes, bleach.  However, one will soften and fray the fibers of your clothing faster than the other- and that one is the one with bleach.  Bleach is very hard on fibers- it whitens, sometimes brightens and if it contains chlorine, it sanitizes, but it also breaks down the fibers faster. So does softener- even faster than the usual amount of bleach in your wash-tub.  That's what softener means: It \"softens\" the clothing by \"softening\" the fibers. My mother had a more succinct explanation:  It rots your clothing. ",
